spans.text: an humble but a grateful Muse : Our Theme is Hope — but of a different kind , The Bane or Blessing of the subject Mind ; This dawning Joy that to the Soul was given , As a short Earnest of its future Heaven : To blame is not the Purpose of my Song , But warn our Sisters not to place it wrong

If trifling Hope has any room to plead
his low Roofs with trickling Showers run
the harsh Usage of a Tyrant Spouse , To see his Mistress in her Woes rejoice , Her Fortune wasted on his guilty Choice , To bear Reproaches doubled on her Ear , Yet only answer with a silent Tear
